title: 820-00426 in S0 state but no chime
message:
I have an A1398 820-00426 board that apparently has all power rails and is in S0 state, with fans spinning, but refuses to chime or start up. USB mouse shows a brief flash, then nothing. No apparent liquid damage. Where would you look next?

ALL_SYS_PWRGD: 3.2V
PPVCC_S0_CPU: 1.8V
SYS_PWROK_R : 3.4V

title: 820-00426 in S0 state but no chime
message:
Any history available, what the client said about the failure?

Could be FDMF6808 problem.
Try known good BIOS, before touching CPU power supply.

title: 820-00426 in S0 state but no chime
message:
The client stated vaguely "The machine developed some sort of heat sensor issue and it quit booting."

I replaced the BIOS chip twice with no change.

title: 820-00426 in S0 state but no chime
message: Probably CPU damage, caused by FDMF6808 chips...

title: 820-00426 in S0 state but no chime
message: Got it, thanks for the diagnosis.
